2. SCP Foundation Content
------------------------------------------------------------

All SCP item names, descriptions, abilities, and other narrative content
used in this game are adapted from works on the SCP Wiki
(https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/) and are licensed under the
Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 3.0 Unported License (CC BY-SA 3.0).

Full license text: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/legalcode

Individual authors are credited on each SCP article page on the SCP Wiki.
A list of source URLs for each SCP item used in this game is available
in `LICENSE-CC-BY-SA-3.0.md` (one URL per article, ordered by SCP id).

The SCP Foundation, its logo, and all associated content are the property
of the SCP Wiki community and its contributors. This is an unofficial
fan project and is not affiliated with, authorized by, or endorsed by
the SCP Foundation, the SCP Wiki, or any of its contributors.

------------------------------------------------------------
3. Combined Work
------------------------------------------------------------

Because this project incorporates SCP content under CC BY-SA 3.0,
the combined work (game data + assets + presentation) is also released
under CC BY-SA 3.0. Anyone redistributing or creating derivative works
must:
  - attribute the SCP Wiki and its contributors,
  - retain the original CC BY-SA 3.0 notice,
  - release derivative works under the same license.

The original code can additionally be reused under the MIT terms above.

